# cursorProxy Project Overview

A lightweight edge-compatible proxy for **DeepSeek**, **Kimi**, **MiniMax**, and **Azure Foundry** (Azure OpenAI Responses API + Azure Anthropic Messages API). Deployed on Vercel Edge, Docker, or EdgeOne Pages.

## What it does

- **Reasoning bridge:** caches provider-specific `reasoning_content` (DeepSeek/Kimi) / `reasoning_details` (MiniMax) by conversation position in KV storage, injects it back on the next turn. Skipped for Azure providers ‚Äî see `azure-foundry.mdc`.
- **Azure Responses chaining:** caches Azure OpenAI response IDs in KV so the next turn can use `previous_response_id` instead of resending the full conversation. See `azure-foundry.mdc`.
- **Claude thinking cache:** caches Claude adaptive-thinking blocks in KV (key prefix `asst:`) so subsequent turns reuse prior reasoning instead of re-thinking from scratch.
- **Vision bridge:** auto-converts inline `image_url` blocks to text descriptions via MiniMax VL-01 (or OpenAI Vision) for text-only models (DeepSeek, MiniMax)
- **Format adapters:** Cursor speaks OpenAI Chat Completions; the proxy translates to/from Azure OpenAI Responses and Azure Anthropic Messages (request body + SSE stream).
- **Model discovery:** serves `GET /v1/models` from `CURSORPROXY_MODELS` env var
- **Auth:** `CURSORPROXY_API_KEY` via `Authorization: Bearer` or `x-api-key` header

## Deployments

- **Vercel Edge:** needs Upstash Redis (`KV_URL` + `KV_TOKEN`). Entry: `api/proxy.js` (`runtime: "edge"`)
- **Docker:** `server.js` wraps the same proxy logic. Uses local Redis via `ioredis` (`REDIS_URL`) or Upstash. Built via GitHub Actions CI ‚Äî pushes to `lqdflying/cursorproxy:latest` on DockerHub
- **EdgeOne Pages:** `edge-functions/` dir, file-based routing, built-in KV (no external Redis needed)

