## Git & GitHub

- **Repo:** `github.com/lqdflying/cursorProxy`
- **CI:** `.github/workflows/docker.yml` ‚Äî builds multi-arch Docker image on push
- **Wiki:** `wiki/` is a **separate git clone** of the GitHub wiki (`git@github.com:lqdflying/cursorProxy.wiki.git`). It is NOT a git submodule ‚Äî there is no `.gitmodules` file, and `wiki/` is listed in `.gitignore` so the main repo never tracks it. Do NOT commit wiki changes in the main repo; cd into `wiki/` (or use `git -C wiki <command>`) and push from that clone. The Shell tool's `working_directory` parameter does not always resolve nested git directories correctly, so prefer `git -C wiki <command>`.
- `.github/instructions/` is in `.gitignore` ‚Äî instructions there are for GitHub UI, not committed
